          "html": "<header>\n  <section class=\"blog-hero-section\" aria-label=\"Blog page header\">\n    <nav class=\"home-navbar\" aria-label=\"Main navigation\">\n      <div class=\"home-nav-container\">\n        <div class=\"home-logo\">\n          <a href=\"/\" class=\"logo-link\" aria-label=\"Webx Design Studio - Go to homepage\">\n            <img src=\"/assets/images/logos/webx-logo.svg\" alt=\"Webx Design Studio\" width=\"140\" height=\"40\" loading=\"eager\" />\n          </a>\n        </div>\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/contact-page.html\" class=\"home-contact-btn\">\n          <span>CONTACT US</span>\n          <svg width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" fill=\"none\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n            <path d=\"M3 13L13 3M13 3H5M13 3V11\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"/>\n          </svg>\n        </a>\n      </div>\n    </nav>\n  </section>\n</header>"
        },
        {
          "id": "blog-section-425f4976",
          "label": "Breadcrumb",
          "enabled": true,
          "html": "<section class=\"breadcrumb-section\" aria-label=\"Breadcrumb\">\n  <div class=\"breadcrumb-container\">\n    <nav class=\"breadcrumb-nav\" aria-label=\"Breadcrumb\">\n      <a href=\"/\" class=\"breadcrumb-link\">Home</a>\n      <span class=\"breadcrumb-separator\" aria-hidden=\"true\">&#8250;</span>\n      <a href=\"/pages/blogs/blogs.html\" class=\"breadcrumb-link\">Blog</a>\n      <span class=\"breadcrumb-separator\" aria-hidden=\"true\">&#8250;</span>\n      <span class=\"breadcrumb-current\" aria-current=\"page\">AI&#8209;Driven Personalization: The UX/UI Design Trend</span>\n    </nav>\n  </div>\n</section>"
        },
        {
          "id": "blog-section-d2726cc0",
          "label": "Blog article featured image",
          "enabled": true,
          "html": "<section class=\"blog-detail-hero\" aria-label=\"Blog article featured image\">\n  <div class=\"blog-hero-image-container\">\n    <img src=\"/assets/images/blogs/blog-img-1.png\" alt=\"AI-Driven Personalization in UX/UI Design 2026 - adaptive interfaces and intelligent user experiences\" class=\"blog-hero-image\" width=\"1200\" height=\"630\" loading=\"eager\" />\n    <div class=\"squiggle squiggle-1\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div>\n    <div class=\"squiggle squiggle-2\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div>\n    <div class=\"squiggle squiggle-3\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div>\n  </div>\n</section>"
        },
        {
          "id": "blog-section-63325511",
          "label": "Blog article content",
          "enabled": true,
          "html": "<section class=\"blog-detail-content\" aria-label=\"Blog article content\">\n  <div class=\"blog-content-container\">\n\n    <!-- Blog Header -->\n    <header class=\"blog-header\">\n      <h1 class=\"blog-title\">AI&#8209;Driven Personalization: The UX/UI Design Trend Your Business Cannot Ignore in 2026</h1>\n\n      <!-- Tags & Date Row -->\n      <div class=\"blog-tags-date-row\">\n        <div class=\"blog-tags\" aria-label=\"Article tags\">\n          <span class=\"blog-tag\">ai personalization ux design</span>\n          <span class=\"blog-tag\">ai in ux ui design</span>\n          <span class=\"blog-tag\">personalized user experience</span>\n        </div>\n        <time class=\"blog-date\" datetime=\"2026-02-07\">Date: 07 Feb 26</time>\n      </div>\n\n      <!-- Social Share -->\n      <div class=\"blog-social-share\" aria-label=\"Share this article\">\n        <a href=\"#\" class=\"blog-social-icon\" aria-label=\"Share on LinkedIn\" id=\"share-linkedin\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n          <img src=\"/assets/images/icons/linkedin-icon.svg\" alt=\"LinkedIn\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        </a>\n        <a href=\"#\" class=\"blog-social-icon\" aria-label=\"Share on Facebook\" id=\"share-facebook\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n          <img src=\"/assets/images/icons/facebook-icon.svg\" alt=\"Facebook\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        </a>\n        <a href=\"#\" class=\"blog-social-icon\" aria-label=\"Share on Twitter\" id=\"share-twitter\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n          <img src=\"/assets/images/icons/twitter-icon.svg\" alt=\"Twitter\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        </a>\n      </div>\n    </header>\n\n    <!-- Blog Body -->\n    <article class=\"blog-article\" itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/BlogPosting\">\n      <meta itemprop=\"headline\" content=\"AI-Driven Personalization: The UX/UI Design Trend Your Business Cannot Ignore in 2026\" />\n      <meta itemprop=\"datePublished\" content=\"2026-02-07\" />\n\n      <p class=\"blog-intro\">\n        In 2026, UX/UI design has shifted from \"one layout fits all\" to interfaces that actually think with your users. Thanks to AI&#8209;driven personalization, websites and apps can now adapt content, layout, and even navigation in real time based on each user's behavior, context, and intent.\n      </p>\n\n      <p class=\"blog-intro\">\n        For business owners, marketers, and product teams, this is not just another buzzword trend. It is becoming the difference between a product users quickly forget and one they keep coming back to.\n      </p>\n\n      <p class=\"blog-intro\">\n        In this article, you will learn what AI&#8209;driven personalization in UX/UI really means, why it is trending in 2026, how it impacts your SEO and conversions, and how your brand can start implementing it with the help of a UX/UI design agency.\n      </p>\n\n      <!-- Section 1 -->\n      <section class=\"blog-page-section\" aria-labelledby=\"section-heading-1\">\n        <h2 class=\"section-heading\" id=\"section-heading-1\">What Is AI&#8209;Driven Personalization in UX/UI?</h2>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">\n          AI&#8209;driven personalization in UX/UI is the practice of using artificial intelligence to tailor the entire digital experience—content, layout, interactions, and flows—to each individual user. Instead of serving the same interface to everyone, AI analyzes data (behavior, clicks, device, location, past actions) and then adjusts the experience in real time.\n        </p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Rather than static \"user segments,\" AI can identify micro&#8209;patterns at scale:</p>\n        <ul class=\"section-list\">\n          <li>Which features a user is likely to need next</li>\n          <li>What type of content format they respond to</li>\n          <li>How much guidance or onboarding support they need</li>\n          <li>When they are most likely to drop off or convert</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">\n          This aligns with broader generative and anticipatory UI trends in 2026, where interfaces adapt proactively instead of passively waiting for clicks.\n        </p>\n      </section>\n\n      <!-- Section 2 -->\n      <section class=\"blog-page-section\" aria-labelledby=\"section-heading-2\">\n        <h2 class=\"section-heading\" id=\"section-heading-2\">Why AI&#8209;Driven Personalization Is the Top UX/UI Trend in 2026</h2>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Several macro&#8209;shifts are pushing personalization to the top of the UX/UI and product design agenda:</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">1. User expectations have changed.</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">People are used to Netflix&#8209;style recommendations, TikTok's \"For You\" feed, and Amazon's product suggestions. Generic experiences feel outdated and irrelevant.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">2. Design is moving from static screens to generative interfaces.</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Generative UIs and on&#8209;demand dynamic interfaces can now rebuild layouts and flows on the fly using AI, based on what a user is trying to do at that moment.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">3. Personalization directly impacts revenue.</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Multiple studies show around 80% of consumers are more likely to buy from brands that personalize their experiences across channels. Personalized UX improves conversion rates, average order value, and retention.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">4. AI tooling has matured.</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Modern design and marketing stacks (e.g., Figma AI, Adobe Sensei, experimentation and personalization tools) make it far easier to analyze behavior and run AI&#8209;driven experiments at scale.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">5. Competitive advantage in crowded markets.</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">In categories where products look similar, an experience that \"understands\" the user and feels uniquely tailored becomes a powerful differentiator.</p>\n      </section>\n\n      <!-- Section 3 -->\n      <section class=\"blog-page-section\" aria-labelledby=\"section-heading-3\">\n        <h2 class=\"section-heading\" id=\"section-heading-3\">Practical Ways to Use AI&#8209;Driven Personalization in Your UX/UI</h2>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Here are concrete, implementation&#8209;ready ideas your brand (and your UX/UI agency) can use.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">1. Adaptive Homepages and Dashboards</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Instead of a single homepage for everyone, AI can:</p>\n        <ul class=\"section-list\">\n          <li>Highlight different hero sections for new vs. returning visitors</li>\n          <li>Re&#8209;order modules (features, case studies, products) by predicted relevance</li>\n          <li>Surface shortcuts or recently used tools in SaaS dashboards</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">This is an extension of \"hyper&#8209;personalized experiences,\" where the interface layout itself adjusts to context and behavior.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">2. Personalized Onboarding Flows</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Onboarding is a critical moment. AI can:</p>\n        <ul class=\"section-list\">\n          <li>Detect user intent (e.g., role, goal, industry) from signup answers and early clicks</li>\n          <li>Create dynamic checklists tailored to that goal</li>\n          <li>Offer extra guidance if the user appears stuck (e.g., hesitating, repeated back&#8209;and&#8209;forth)</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Design teams are already seeing AI&#8209;driven onboarding increase feature adoption and reduce early churn.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">3. Context&#8209;Aware Content and Product Recommendations</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Go beyond \"customers also bought\":</p>\n        <ul class=\"section-list\">\n          <li>E&#8209;commerce: Recommend products based on browsing depth, price sensitivity, and style preferences</li>\n          <li>B2B SaaS: Suggest relevant guides, webinars, or in&#8209;app tips based on features visited</li>\n          <li>Media: Re&#8209;rank articles or videos based on reading history and completion rates</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">This ties directly into the trend of anticipatory design—surfacing what the user is likely to need before they explicitly search for it.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">4. Dynamic Micro&#8209;Interactions and Feedback</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">AI can also personalize how the interface feels:</p>\n        <ul class=\"section-list\">\n          <li>More micro&#8209;copy or hints for users who seem unsure</li>\n          <li>Faster, more direct paths for expert or power users</li>\n          <li>Adjusted timing and type of nudges (e.g., subtle toast vs. blocking modal)</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Lively, responsive interfaces that \"react\" to the user's behavior are a core UI trend in 2026.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">5. Inclusive and Accessible Personalization</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">AI can help tailor experiences for accessibility:</p>\n        <ul class=\"section-list\">\n          <li>Automatically adjusting font size, contrast, or interaction patterns based on user preferences</li>\n          <li>Detecting interaction issues (e.g., repeated mis&#8209;taps) and adapting components</li>\n          <li>Supporting neuro&#8209;inclusion with options for reduced motion, simplified layouts, or alternative navigation paths</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">This is not only ethically important, but also improves overall satisfaction and retention across diverse user groups.</p>\n      </section>\n\n      <!-- Section 4 -->\n      <section class=\"blog-page-section\" aria-labelledby=\"section-heading-4\">\n        <h2 class=\"section-heading\" id=\"section-heading-4\">How AI&#8209;Personalized UX Impacts SEO and Conversions</h2>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Personalization is not only good UX—it is also smart SEO.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">UX Signals and Search Rankings</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Google's Core Web Vitals and page experience signals are essentially UX metrics: loading speed, interactivity, and visual stability. When AI&#8209;driven personalization is done right, it can:</p>\n        <ul class=\"section-list\">\n          <li>Reduce bounce rates (users find what they need faster)</li>\n          <li>Increase time on site and pages per session</li>\n          <li>Improve conversion and micro&#8209;conversion rates (signups, demo requests, cart adds)</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">These behavioral signals contribute to better long&#8209;term search performance, even if \"UX\" itself is not a direct ranking factor.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">AI Search and Zero&#8209;Click SERPs in 2026</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">In 2026, SEO is increasingly defined by AI search experiences like Google's AI Overviews, Bing Copilot, and multimodal search.</p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">AI&#8209;powered search systems:</p>\n        <ul class=\"section-list\">\n          <li>Prefer content that clearly explains topics, user journeys, and problems</li>\n          <li>Pull structured, well&#8209;marked sections (FAQs, lists, tables) directly into their results</li>\n          <li>Reward brands that show topical authority and real experience (E&#8209;E&#8209;A&#8209;T 2.0)</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">If your product delivers great, personalized UX and your content explains that value clearly, AI search is more likely to surface your brand as a trusted source.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">Better UX = Higher Conversion Rates</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">From a business perspective, personalization influences almost every revenue metric:</p>\n        <ul class=\"section-list\">\n          <li>Higher add&#8209;to&#8209;cart and checkout completion in e&#8209;commerce</li>\n          <li>More demo bookings and trial signups in SaaS</li>\n          <li>Stronger engagement and content consumption for media and education platforms</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Agencies that combine UX/UI design, AI, and CRO (conversion rate optimization) are seeing substantial improvements in funnel performance when personalization is integrated into core flows, not just as an afterthought.</p>\n      </section>\n\n      <!-- Section 5 -->\n      <section class=\"blog-page-section\" aria-labelledby=\"section-heading-5\">\n        <h2 class=\"section-heading\" id=\"section-heading-5\">How to Get Started with AI&#8209;Driven Personalization</h2>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">You do not need to redesign your entire product on day one. Here is a practical rollout roadmap you can follow with your UX/UI design agency:</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">1. Clarify business goals.</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Decide what you want to move first: signups, activation, feature adoption, revenue per user, or retention.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">2. Map key journeys and friction points.</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Audit your current UX: Where do users drop off? Which pages get traffic but low engagement? Which features are under&#8209;used?</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">3. Choose 1–2 high&#8209;impact personalization use cases.</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Examples:</p>\n        <ul class=\"section-list\">\n          <li>Personalized homepage hero for new vs. existing customers</li>\n          <li>Role&#8209;based onboarding flows</li>\n          <li>AI&#8209;driven recommendations on product or pricing pages</li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">4. Set up your data and tooling.</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Work with design and engineering to:</p>\n        <ul class=\"section-list\">\n          <li>Track key events (clicks, views, form interactions, purchases)</li>\n          <li>Integrate an experimentation/personalization platform</li>\n          <li>Ensure privacy and consent mechanisms are in place</li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">5. Design and test personalized variants.</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Your UX/UI team designs multiple variants; AI decides which one to serve based on user data. Run experiments until you see statistically significant lift.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">6. Scale what works; retire what doesn't.</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Once a pattern proves successful, roll it out broadly. Keep testing new ideas in other parts of the journey.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">7. Continuously monitor and refine.</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">AI personalization is not \"set and forget.\" Monitor performance, watch for bias, and keep improving the experience over time.</p>\n      </section>\n\n      <!-- Section 6 -->\n      <section class=\"blog-page-section\" aria-labelledby=\"section-heading-6\">\n        <h2 class=\"section-heading\" id=\"section-heading-6\">Common Pitfalls and Ethical Considerations</h2>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">While powerful, AI&#8209;driven personalization must be handled carefully.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">Over&#8209;personalization creepiness</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Users should feel understood, not surveilled. Avoid using sensitive signals (e.g., health, finances) in a way that feels intrusive. Be transparent about data usage.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">Algorithmic bias</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">If your training data is biased, your personalization will be too. Regularly audit recommendations and experiences for fairness and inclusivity.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">Performance and Core Web Vitals</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Heavy personalization scripts can slow pages down. Work with your UX/UI and engineering teams to optimize performance—slow, \"smart\" experiences will still lose users.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">Privacy and compliance</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Ensure compliance with regulations (GDPR, local data laws) and give users clear opt&#8209;in/opt&#8209;out controls for personalized experiences.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Working with an experienced UX/UI agency that understands both AI and ethical design can help you avoid these mistakes.</p>\n      </section>\n\n      <!-- Section 7 - FAQs -->\n      <section class=\"blog-page-section\" aria-labelledby=\"section-heading-7\">\n        <h2 class=\"section-heading\" id=\"section-heading-7\">FAQs: AI&#8209;Driven Personalization in UX/UI</h2>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">1. Is AI&#8209;driven personalization only for big tech companies?</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">No. While large platforms pioneered personalization, modern tools have made it accessible to startups and mid&#8209;size businesses as well. Even simple use cases—like role&#8209;based dashboards or basic content recommendations—can be implemented without massive data science teams.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">2. How much data do we need to start?</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">You do not need \"big data\" to begin. Start with the data you already have: page views, clicks, sessions, form submissions, and purchase events. Over time, as you collect more interactions, your personalization models become smarter and more granular.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">3. Will AI replace UX/UI designers?</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">AI will not replace designers; it changes what they focus on. Instead of manually designing endless static variations, designers can use AI to generate options, run experiments faster, and spend more time understanding users, solving real problems, and crafting strategy.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"section-text\"><strong style=\"color: #fff;\">4. How does AI&#8209;driven personalization help my SEO?</strong></p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">Personalized UX improves engagement metrics like bounce rate, time on site, and conversion rate, all of which support better long&#8209;term search performance. In an AI&#8209;driven search world, brands that provide clear, helpful, human&#8209;centric experiences—and explain them well in their content—will earn more visibility.</p>\n      </section>\n\n      <!-- Section 8 - Final Thoughts -->\n      <section class=\"blog-page-section\" aria-labelledby=\"section-heading-8\">\n        <h2 class=\"section-heading\" id=\"section-heading-8\">Final Thoughts: Turn AI&#8209;Powered UX Into a Competitive Advantage</h2>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">\n          AI&#8209;driven personalization is not just another UX/UI trend for 2026. It is a fundamental shift in how digital products are designed, delivered, and optimized. Brands that embrace it now will build experiences that feel intuitive, human, and unforgettable—while also improving SEO, conversions, and customer lifetime value.\n        </p>\n        <p class=\"section-text\">\n          Want to see what AI&#8209;driven personalization could look like for your website or app? Our UX/UI design team at Webx helps brands design data&#8209;driven, AI&#8209;powered experiences that convert. <a href=\"/pages/main/contact-page.html\" style=\"color: #00d4ff; text-decoration: underline;\">Contact us today</a> to schedule a free strategy session.\n        </p>\n      </section>\n\n    </article>\n\n  </div>\n</section>"
        },
        {
          "id": "blog-section-ac479389",
          "label": "More blog posts",
          "enabled": true,
          "html": "<section class=\"blog-section animate-section\" aria-label=\"More blog posts\">\n  <div class=\"blog-container\">\n\n    <div class=\"section-header animate-fade-in\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Today&#39;s Blogs</p>\n      <h2 class=\"section-title\">Check out our blog for the latest tips, tricks, and happenings in business and design.</h2>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"blog-slider-wrapper\">\n      <div class=\"blog-slider animate-cards\" role=\"list\">\n\n        <!-- Blog Card 2 -->\n        <article class=\"blog-card\" role=\"listitem\">\n          <div class=\"blog-image\">\n            <img src=\"/assets/images/blogs/blog-img-2.png\" alt=\"Apple UX design study - 10 lessons from Apple's product design philosophy for 2026\" width=\"400\" height=\"250\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"blog-content\">\n            <h3 class=\"blog-card-title\">Apple Design Study: 10 UX Lessons You Can Apply to Your Products in 2026</h3>\n            <div class=\"blog-meta\">\n              <div class=\"blog-tags\" aria-label=\"Tags\">\n                <span class=\"blog-tag\">apple design study</span>\n                <span class=\"blog-tag\">apple ux case study</span>\n                <span class=\"blog-tag\">ios design principles</span>\n              </div>\n              <time class=\"blog-date\" datetime=\"2025-04-16\">Date: 16 Apr&#39; 25</time>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"blog-excerpt\">Apple is not just a tech company; it is a masterclass in product design and user experience. From the first iPhone to the latest visionOS interfaces, Apple has consistently set the bar for how digital products should look, feel, and behave.</p>\n            <a href=\"/pages/blogs/blog-apple.html\" class=\"blog-read-more\" aria-label=\"Read more about Apple Design Study: 10 UX Lessons\">\n              <span>READ MORE</span>\n              <svg width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" fill=\"none\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n                <path d=\"M3 13L13 3M13 3H5M13 3V11\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" />\n              </svg>\n            </a>\n          </div>\n        </article>\n\n        <!-- Blog Card 3 -->\n        <article class=\"blog-card\" role=\"listitem\">\n          <div class=\"blog-image\">\n            <img src=\"/assets/images/blogs/blog-img-3.png\" alt=\"High-converting landing page UX design guide 2026 - CRO and conversion optimization strategies\" width=\"400\" height=\"250\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"blog-content\">\n            <h3 class=\"blog-card-title\">How to Design a High-Converting Landing Page in 2026 (UX + CRO Complete Guide)</h3>\n            <div class=\"blog-meta\">\n              <div class=\"blog-tags\" aria-label=\"Tags\">\n                <span class=\"blog-tag\">high converting landing page</span>\n                <span class=\"blog-tag\">landing page ux design</span>\n                <span class=\"blog-tag\">conversion rate optimization</span>\n              </div>\n              <time class=\"blog-date\" datetime=\"2026-02-18\">Date: 18 Feb 26</time>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"blog-excerpt\">Your landing page is often the final gateway between a visitor's interest and a real business action — whether that is a signup, a purchase, a demo booking, or a lead form submission. It does not matter how good your ads are or how much traffic you drive — if the landing page fails to convert, the entire funnel breaks.</p>\n            <a href=\"/pages/blogs/blog-3.html\" class=\"blog-read-more\" aria-label=\"Read more about How to Design a High-Converting Landing Page in 2026\">\n              <span>READ MORE</span>\n              <svg width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" fill=\"none\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n                <path d=\"M3 13L13 3M13 3H5M13 3V11\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" />\n              </svg>\n            </a>\n          </div>\n        </article>\n\n        <!-- Blog Card 4 -->\n        <article class=\"blog-card\" role=\"listitem\">\n          <div class=\"blog-image\">\n            <img src=\"/assets/images/blogs/blog-img-4.png\" alt=\"10 signs it is time to redesign your website in 2026 - website redesign checklist and warning signs\" width=\"400\" height=\"250\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"blog-content\">\n            <h3 class=\"blog-card-title\">10 Signs It&#39;s Time to Redesign Your Website in 2026 (+ Full Redesign Checklist)</h3>\n            <div class=\"blog-meta\">\n              <div class=\"blog-tags\" aria-label=\"Tags\">\n                <span class=\"blog-tag\">website redesign 2026</span>\n                <span class=\"blog-tag\">when to redesign website</span>\n                <span class=\"blog-tag\">website redesign checklist</span>\n              </div>\n              <time class=\"blog-date\" datetime=\"2026-02-18\">Date: 18 Feb 26</time>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"blog-excerpt\">Most businesses redesign their website too late. By the time they finally decide to act, their website has already been quietly losing them traffic, leads, and revenue for months — sometimes years — without them realising it.</p>\n            <a href=\"/pages/details/de-pdp.html\" class=\"blog-read-more\" aria-label=\"Read more about 10 Signs It is Time to Redesign Your Website in 2026\">\n              <span>READ MORE</span>\n              <svg width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" fill=\"none\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n                <path d=\"M3 13L13 3M13 3H5M13 3V11\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" />\n              </svg>\n            </a>\n          </div>\n        </article>\n\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"blog-slider-controls\">\n      <div class=\"blog-progress-bar\" role=\"progressbar\" aria-label=\"Blog slider progress\">\n        <div class=\"blog-progress-bg\"></div>\n        <div class=\"blog-progress-fill\"></div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"blog-navigation\">\n        <button class=\"blog-arrow blog-prev\" aria-label=\"Previous blog post\">&#8592;</button>\n        <button class=\"blog-arrow blog-next\" aria-label=\"Next blog post\">&#8594;</button>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n  </div>\n</section>"
        },
        {
          "id": "blog-section-72b9317b",
          "label": "Site footer",
          "enabled": true,
          "html": "<footer class=\"footer-section\" aria-label=\"Site footer\">\n  <div class=\"footer-container\">\n    <div class=\"footer-top\">\n      <div class=\"footer-logo\">\n        <img src=\"/assets/images/logos/webx-logo.svg\" alt=\"Webx Design Studio\" class=\"footer-logo-img\" width=\"140\" height=\"40\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"footer-social\">\n        <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/piyushgohil8889/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"social-icon\" aria-label=\"Webx Design Studio on LinkedIn\">\n          <img src=\"/assets/images/icons/linkedin-icon.png\" alt=\"LinkedIn\" class=\"social-icon-img\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        </a>\n        <a href=\"https://dribbble.com/desinger8889\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"social-icon\" aria-label=\"Webx Design Studio on Dribbble\">\n          <img src=\"/assets/images/icons/dribbble-icon.png\" alt=\"Dribbble\" class=\"social-icon-img\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        </a>\n        <a href=\"https://www.behance.net/Piyushgohil8889\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"social-icon\" aria-label=\"Webx Design Studio on Behance\">\n          <img src=\"/assets/images/icons/behance-icon.png\" alt=\"Behance\" class=\"social-icon-img\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        </a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"footer-section-block\">\n      <h3 class=\"footer-heading\">\n        Services\n        <button class=\"footer-toggle\" aria-label=\"Toggle Services menu\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"accordion-arrow-circle\">\n            <svg class=\"arrow-svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http:/www.w3.org/2000/svg\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n              <path d=\"M5 12H19M19 12L12 5M19 12L12 19\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" />\n            </svg>\n          </span>\n        </button>\n      </h3>\n      <div class=\"footer-links\">\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/services.html\">UI/UX Design</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/services.html\">Web Design</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/services.html\">App Design</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/services.html\">Marketing Emailer</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/services.html\">Social Media</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/services.html\">Logo Design</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/services.html\">Graphics Design</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/services.html\">Tool Design</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/services.html\">Document Design</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/services.html\">ETC Design</a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"footer-section-block\">\n      <h3 class=\"footer-heading\">\n        Company\n        <button class=\"footer-toggle\" aria-label=\"Toggle Company menu\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n          <span class=\"accordion-arrow-circle\">\n            <svg class=\"arrow-svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http:/www.w3.org/2000/svg\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n              <path d=\"M5 12H19M19 12L12 5M19 12L12 19\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" />\n            </svg>\n          </span>\n        </button>\n      </h3>\n      <div class=\"footer-links\">\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/about.html\">About Us</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/blogs/blogs.html\">Blog</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/main/contact-page.html\">Contact</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/legal/privacy-policy.html\">Privacy Policy</a>\n        <a href=\"/pages/legal/term-condition.html\">Terms of Service</a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"footer-bottom\">\n      <p class=\"footer-copyright\">&copy; 2026 Webx Design Studio. All rights reserved</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"footer-bg-text\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    <img src=\"/assets/images/logos/webx-footer-logo-lar